<text id="04-procedure" title="pytest Project Setup — Procedure" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="800" depth="medium">
  <summary>Step-by-step procedure for applying python-pytest-setup.</summary>

    <section title="Step 1: Install plugins">
      <p>Input: uv available</p>
      <p>Action: uv add --dev pytest pytest-cov pytest-xdist pytest-mock pytest-asyncio (if async).</p>
      <p>Output: Plugin set ready.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 2: Write pyproject config">
      <p>Input: Plugins installed</p>
      <p>Action: [tool.pytest.ini_options] with DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE (if Django), addopts='--strict-markers --cov --cov-fail-under=80'.</p>
      <p>Output: Config canonical.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 3: Set up tests/ structure">
      <p>Input: src/ exists</p>
      <p>Action: Mirror src/&lt;package&gt;/&lt;module&gt;.py → tests/&lt;package&gt;/test_&lt;module&gt;.py.</p>
      <p>Output: Discovery deterministic.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 4: Write first failing test">
      <p>Input: Test path</p>
      <p>Action: Test for an unimplemented feature.</p>
      <p>Output: Red.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 5: Minimal code to green">
      <p>Input: Failing test</p>
      <p>Action: Implement just enough.</p>
      <p>Output: Green.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 6: Wire CI">
      <p>Input: Tests green locally</p>
      <p>Action: Add CI step: pytest -n auto --cov.</p>
      <p>Output: Same gate in CI.</p>
    </section>
</text>
